  </div>

  <div class="prev-panel active" id="prev-travel">
    <div class="prev-card"><div class="prev-icon">🚕</div><div class="prev-title">Verify Your Cab Before Boarding</div><div class="prev-text">Always check cab number, driver name and photo before getting in.</div><ul class="prev-points"><li>Screenshot the ride details and WhatsApp it to a trusted contact</li><li>Sit behind the driver — never in the front passenger seat</li><li>Share your trip via app's built-in sharing feature</li><li>Cancel and rebook if anything feels off — trust your gut</li></ul></div>
    <div class="prev-card"><div class="prev-icon">🚌</div><div class="prev-title">Bus & Public Transport in MP</div><div class="prev-text">MP's city buses have women-reserved sections — always use them.</div><ul class="prev-points"><li>Stand near the conductor or driver in an empty bus</li><li>Use women's reserved seating at all times</li><li>Avoid isolated bus stops after 8PM — wait at shops/petrol pumps</li><li>Bhopal City Link buses have women marshals — report to them</li></ul></div>
    <div class="prev-card"><div class="prev-icon">📍</div><div class="prev-title">Share Live Location Always</div><div class="prev-text">Make it a daily habit — not just when you feel scared.</div><ul class="prev-points"><li>Google Maps "Share Live Location" with parent for every solo trip</li><li>Tell someone your exact route, departure and arrival time</li><li>Have a secret family code word: e.g. "call the doctor" = call police</li><li>Check in every 30 minutes on long journeys</li></ul></div>
    <div class="prev-card"><div class="prev-icon">🚆</div><div class="prev-title">Train Travel Safety — MP</div><div class="prev-text">All major MP stations (Bhopal, Indore, Jabalpur, Gwalior, Ujjain) have RPF.</div><ul class="prev-points"><li>Book confirmed berths — lower/middle in women-only or general coaches</li><li>Call RPF at 182 immediately if harassed on the train or platform</li><li>Lock your berth chain at night — do not open without verifying</li><li>Prefer IRCTC app booking so your trip is digitally tracked</li></ul></div>
    <div class="prev-card"><div class="prev-icon">🔋</div><div class="prev-title">Keep Your Phone Emergency-Ready</div><div class="prev-text">A dead phone in an emergency is as dangerous as no phone.</div><ul class="prev-points"><li>Carry a power bank (min 10,000 mAh) every time you go out</li><li>Save emergency contacts as "ICE Mom", "ICE Dad" at top of phonebook</li><li>Enable power-button SOS: press volume down + power 5 times on Android</li><li>Keep mobile data on at all times when travelling alone</li></ul></div>
    <div class="prev-card"><div class="prev-icon">🛺</div><div class="prev-title">Auto-Rickshaw Safety in MP Cities</div><div class="prev-text">Autos are the most common transport in Bhopal, Indore — stay safe.</div><ul class="prev-points"><li>Note the auto registration number before boarding — screenshot it</li><li>Make a loud fake call stating your destination before sitting</li><li>Prefer autos at official stands or app-based Rapido/Ola autos</li><li>Do not take autos through deserted routes late at night</li></ul></div>
  </div>

  <div class="prev-panel" id="prev-digital">
    <div class="prev-card"><div class="prev-icon">🔒</div><div class="prev-title">Social Media Privacy</div><div class="prev-text">Your online presence can expose you to real-world dangers.</div><ul class="prev-points"><li>Set Instagram, Facebook, and Snapchat to Private</li><li>Never post your daily routine, college timings, or home address</li><li>Turn off location tags on all photos before posting</li><li>Disable "People Nearby" on WhatsApp and dating apps</li></ul></div>
    <div class="prev-card"><div class="prev-icon">📵</div><div class="prev-title">Protect Against Cyber Stalking</div><div class="prev-text">Block, screenshot, report — always in this order.</div><ul class="prev-points"><li>Screenshot all harassing messages first — then block</li><li>Report to cybercrime.gov.in or call 1930 with screenshots</li><li>Do not engage or respond to harassers — ever</li><li>Use different usernames across different platforms</li></ul></div>
    <div class="prev-card"><div class="prev-icon">🖼️</div><div class="prev-title">Prevent Photo & Video Misuse</div><div class="prev-text">Non-consensual sharing is a criminal offense under IT Act.</div><ul class="prev-points"><li>Never share intimate photos with anyone — no exceptions</li><li>Check which apps have camera and gallery access — revoke unnecessary ones</li><li>Enable two-step verification on all accounts immediately</li><li>Report morphed images to 1930 — action within 24 hours is mandated</li></ul></div>
    <div class="prev-card"><div class="prev-icon">💳</div><div class="prev-title">Online Financial Safety</div><div class="prev-text">Cyber fraud often targets women through emotional manipulation.</div><ul class="prev-points"><li>Never share OTP with anyone — even if they claim to be bank, police or government</li><li>Verify job offers and matrimonial profiles carefully before engaging</li><li>No legitimate organization ever asks for money upfront</li><li>Report financial fraud at 1930 immediately — golden hour matters</li></ul></div>
    <div class="prev-card"><div class="prev-icon">📱</div><div class="prev-title">Install Safety Apps</div><div class="prev-text">These apps can save your life in seconds.</div><ul class="prev-points"><li>Himmat Plus (Delhi Police) — shake to send SOS with GPS</li><li>bSafe — has a fake call feature and follower mode</li><li>Shake2Safety — works even when screen is locked</li><li>MP Police app — direct complaint filing from Madhya Pradesh</li></ul></div>
    <div class="prev-card"><div class="prev-icon">🧨</div><div class="prev-title">Online Dating & Meeting Safety</div><div class="prev-text">Always verify before meeting someone from online.</div><ul class="prev-points"><li>Video call before first meeting — verify it's a real person</li><li>Always meet for the first time in a public, busy place</li><li>Tell a trusted person your exact meeting location and time</li><li>Never share your home address with someone you just met online</li></ul></div>
  </div>



  <div class="prev-panel" id="prev-night">
    <div class="prev-card"><div class="prev-icon">🌙</div><div class="prev-title">Walking Alone at Night in MP Cities</div><div class="prev-text">Bhopal, Indore, Gwalior — stay on lit, busy roads always.</div><ul class="prev-points"><li>Stay on well-lit, busy roads even if it means a longer route</li><li>Avoid shortcuts through parks, alleys, and isolated lanes — day or night</li><li>Walk confidently and with purpose — don't look lost or distracted</li><li>Keep your phone in hand with 112 ready to dial in one tap</li></ul></div>
    <div class="prev-card"><div class="prev-icon">🔦</div><div class="prev-title">Equip Yourself Before Going Out</div><div class="prev-text">Simple items that dramatically increase your safety.</div><ul class="prev-points"><li>Personal alarm (loud siren) — available on Amazon for ₹150-300</li><li>Pepper spray is legal in India — carry it in an accessible pocket, not your bag</li><li>Keep your keys in hand when approaching your vehicle or home</li><li>Charge your phone to 100% and carry a power bank every time</li></ul></div>
    <div class="prev-card"><div class="prev-icon">🛑</div><div class="prev-title">If You Feel Followed</div><div class="prev-text">Do not panic — act immediately and smartly.</div><ul class="prev-points"><li>Enter the nearest open shop, petrol pump, restaurant or dhaba immediately</li><li>Do NOT go home directly — never reveal your actual address to a follower</li><li>Shout "FIRE!" loudly — more people respond than to "Help" or "Bachao"</li><li>Call 100 or 112 and describe your exact location clearly</li></ul></div>
    <div class="prev-card"><div class="prev-icon">📞</div><div class="prev-title">Fake Call Technique</div><div class="prev-text">A simple trick that has helped thousands of women.</div><ul class="prev-points"><li>Pretend to be on a call if you feel followed or uncomfortable</li><li>Say loudly: "I am near [landmark], reaching in 5 minutes, bhaiya wait karo"</li><li>Some apps like bSafe simulate incoming calls on demand</li><li>This buys time to assess and move toward a safer location</li></ul></div>
  </div>

  <div class="prev-panel" id="prev-home">
    <div class="prev-card"><div class="prev-icon">🔐</div><div class="prev-title">Home Security Basics</div><div class="prev-text">Your home should be your safest space.</div><ul class="prev-points"><li>Never open the door without verifying — use peephole or intercom</li><li>Keep a door chain/stopper on while sleeping</li><li>Know all entry points to your residence</li><li>Keep a fully charged phone on your bedside every night</li></ul></div>
    <div class="prev-card"><div class="prev-icon">🤝</div><div class="prev-title">Build a Neighbourhood Network</div><div class="prev-text">A strong community is the best security system.</div><ul class="prev-points"><li>Introduce yourself to at least 2-3 trusted neighbours</li><li>Share emergency contact numbers with them</li><li>Join your housing society's WhatsApp group</li><li>Look out for strangers loitering near your building and alert neighbours</li></ul></div>
    <div class="prev-card"><div class="prev-icon">🚪</div><div class="prev-title">Verify People Entering Your Home</div><div class="prev-text">Background-check everyone who enters your home.</div><ul class="prev-points"><li>Verify Aadhaar of domestic helpers before hiring</li><li>Register domestic workers at your local police station (it's free)</li><li>Use verified platforms like UrbanClap for plumbers, electricians etc.</li><li>Never let unverified servicemen in when you are alone at home</li></ul></div>
  </div>

  <div class="prev-panel" id="prev-workplace">
    <div class="prev-card"><div class="prev-icon">💼</div><div class="prev-title">Know the POSH Act Fully</div><div class="prev-text">The law is completely on your side at every workplace.</div><ul class="prev-points"><li>Every workplace with 10+ employees must have a functioning ICC</li><li>Complaint must be filed within 3 months of the incident</li><li>You are fully protected from retaliation after filing a complaint</li><li>If your workplace ICC fails, complain to Local Complaints Committee (LCC)</li></ul></div>
    <div class="prev-card"><div class="prev-icon">📝</div><div class="prev-title">Document Everything — Build Evidence</div><div class="prev-text">Evidence is your strongest weapon.</div><ul class="prev-points"><li>Save harassing messages, emails, chats as screenshots immediately</li><li>Note dates, times, witnesses, and exact words used</li><li>Keep a private written diary of incidents with dates and details</li><li>Store all evidence on cloud storage — not just on your phone</li></ul></div>
    <div class="prev-card"><div class="prev-icon">🌃</div><div class="prev-title">Night Shift Safety — Your Legal Rights</div><div class="prev-text">Employers are legally required to ensure your safety.</div><ul class="prev-points"><li>Company must provide cab with a female security guard for night shifts</li><li>Share your cab details with family before every night shift</li><li>Travel with a colleague whenever possible</li><li>Report non-compliance to Labour Department or call 1800-11-8066</li></ul></div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══════════ 4. SAFETY TIPS ══════════ -->
<section id="tips">
  <div class="section-tag" style="background:rgba(0,188,212,.15);color:var(--teal);">💡 Daily Habits</div>
  <h2 class="section-title">Essential <span style="color:var(--teal)">Safety Tips</span></h2>
  <p class="section-sub">Small daily habits that build a powerful protective shield around you.</p>
  <div class="tips-grid reveal">
    <div class="tip-card"><div class="tip-num">01</div><div class="tip-icon">📱</div><div class="tip-title">Share Live Location Always</div><div class="tip-text">Whenever travelling alone — day or night — share your live location via Google Maps with a parent or friend. Make it a non-negotiable daily habit.</div></div>
    <div class="tip-card"><div class="tip-num">02</div><div class="tip-icon">🔋</div><div class="tip-title">Phone Charged = You're Armed</div><div class="tip-text">Treat battery like fuel. Carry a power bank always. Save ICE contacts (In Case of Emergency) at the top of your phonebook. Enable one-press SOS on your phone settings.</div></div>
    <div class="tip-card"><div class="tip-num">03</div><div class="tip-icon">🚕</div><div class="tip-title">Verify Every Ride</div><div class="tip-text">Match cab number, driver name and photo before entering. Screenshot and send to family. Sit behind the driver. Make a vocal call stating your destination before moving.</div></div>
    <div class="tip-card"><div class="tip-num">04</div><div class="tip-icon">👀</div><div class="tip-title">Stay Aware — One Earphone Off</div><div class="tip-text">Never use both earphones in unfamiliar areas. You need to hear your surroundings. Keep one ear free when walking alone on quiet roads or at night.</div></div>
    <div class="tip-card"><div class="tip-num">05</div><div class="tip-icon">🛡️</div><div class="tip-title">Install Safety Apps</div><div class="tip-text">Himmat Plus, bSafe, or Shake2Safety. Enable them and test with family. The MP Police app allows direct complaint filing from anywhere in Madhya Pradesh.</div></div>
    <div class="tip-card"><div class="tip-num">06</div><div class="tip-icon">🗣️</div><div class="tip-title">Trust Your Instincts Completely</div><div class="tip-text">If something feels wrong — it is wrong. Leave immediately. You do not owe anyone an explanation. Your safety always comes first — no exceptions.</div></div>
    <div class="tip-card"><div class="tip-num">07</div><div class="tip-icon">🔑</div><div class="tip-title">Carry Keys & Pepper Spray</div><div class="tip-text">Keep keys in hand when approaching your vehicle or home — not buried in your bag. Pepper spray is legal in India, fits in any pocket, and is highly effective.</div></div>
    <div class="tip-card"><div class="tip-num">08</div><div class="tip-icon">📸</div><div class="tip-title">Screenshot First — Then Block</div><div class="tip-text">If harassed online — screenshot everything first as evidence, then block and report. Don't delete anything before reporting to 1930. Evidence is your power.</div></div>
  </div>
</section>

