<!-- ══════════ 6. SELF DEFENSE ══════════ -->
<section id="selfdefense">
  <div class="section-tag" style="background:rgba(255,112,67,.15);color:var(--orange);">🥋 Protect Yourself</div>
  <h2 class="section-title">Self Defense <span style="color:var(--orange)">Techniques</span></h2>
  <p class="section-sub">No experience needed. These moves create 2-5 seconds — enough time to escape.</p>
  <div class="defense-grid reveal">
    <div class="defense-card"><div class="dc-header"><div class="dc-icon" style="background:rgba(255,61,139,.2);">👊</div><div><div class="dc-title">Wrist Grab Escape</div><div class="dc-level">⭐ Beginner — Learn this first</div></div></div><ul class="dc-steps"><li>Rotate your wrist toward the attacker's thumb — the weakest grip point</li><li>Pull sharply toward your own body in one swift motion</li><li>Step back immediately to create distance</li><li>Shout loudly to attract bystanders, then run</li></ul></div>
    <div class="defense-card"><div class="dc-header"><div class="dc-icon" style="background:rgba(0,188,212,.2);">🦵</div><div><div class="dc-title">Knee Strike</div><div class="dc-level">⭐ Beginner — High impact</div></div></div><ul class="dc-steps"><li>If grabbed from the front — do not struggle yet, stay calm</li><li>Grab the attacker's shoulders or clothing for balance</li><li>Drive your knee sharply upward into the groin with full force</li><li>Run and shout immediately — do not wait to assess their reaction</li></ul></div>
    <div class="defense-card"><div class="dc-header"><div class="dc-icon" style="background:rgba(124,58,237,.2);">🤜</div><div><div class="dc-title">Palm Strike to Nose</div><div class="dc-level">⭐⭐ Intermediate</div></div></div><ul class="dc-steps"><li>Fingers bent back, palm flat and firm — NOT a closed fist</li><li>Strike sharply upward toward the bridge of the nose</li><li>Drive from your hip — use whole body weight, not just arm</li><li>Follow with a second strike if needed, then escape immediately</li></ul></div>
    <div class="defense-card"><div class="dc-header"><div class="dc-icon" style="background:rgba(255,214,0,.2);">😤</div><div><div class="dc-title">Bear Hug Escape</div><div class="dc-level">⭐⭐ Intermediate</div></div></div><ul class="dc-steps"><li>The moment grabbed from behind — drop your weight suddenly by bending knees</li><li>Stomp hard on the attacker's foot with your heel</li><li>Throw your head backward sharply into their face</li><li>Spin, elbow strike to the ribs, run immediately</li></ul></div>
    <div class="defense-card"><div class="dc-header"><div class="dc-icon" style="background:rgba(0,230,118,.2);">🔑</div><div><div class="dc-title">Keys &amp; Objects as Tools</div><div class="dc-level">⭐ Beginner — Always Accessible</div></div></div><ul class="dc-steps"><li>Hold keys between fingers when walking alone at night</li><li>A firm jab with keys to the face creates an opening to escape</li><li>Pepper spray is legal in India and highly effective — carry it always</li><li>Any rigid object (umbrella, water bottle) can be used defensively</li></ul></div>
    <div class="defense-card"><div class="dc-header"><div class="dc-icon" style="background:rgba(255,112,67,.2);">🧠</div><div><div class="dc-title">Mental Preparedness</div><div class="dc-level">⭐ The Most Important Defense</div></div></div><ul class="dc-steps"><li>Stay aware at all times — no earphones in both ears ever</li><li>Make confident eye contact — it signals you are not an easy target</li><li>Shout "FIRE!" not "Help" — people respond to fire much faster</li><li>Trust your gut instantly — if it feels wrong, leave before you can even analyse why</li></ul></div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══════════ 7. RIGHTS ══════════ -->
<section id="rights">
  <div class="section-tag" style="background:rgba(124,58,237,.15);color:var(--purple);">⚖️ Know Your Rights</div>
  <h2 class="section-title">Women's Rights <span style="color:var(--purple)">& Indian Laws</span></h2>
  <p class="section-sub">These laws are your legal shield. Know them — and use them without hesitation.</p>
  <div class="rights-grid reveal">
    <div class="right-card"><div class="rc-tag" style="background:rgba(255,61,139,.15);color:var(--pink);">Workplace</div><div class="rc-title">POSH Act — Sexual Harassment at Work</div><div class="rc-text">Every workplace with 10+ employees must have a functioning ICC. File within 3 months. Your identity is protected and retaliation against you is a separate punishable offense.</div><div class="rc-year">Sexual Harassment of Women at Workplace Act, 2013</div></div>
    <div class="right-card"><div class="rc-tag" style="background:rgba(0,188,212,.15);color:var(--teal);">Home Safety</div><div class="rc-title">Domestic Violence Protection</div><div class="rc-text">Physical, emotional, sexual, verbal, and economic abuse are ALL covered. You can get a Protection Order, Residence Order (right to stay in shared home), and Monetary Relief — even against in-laws.</div><div class="rc-year">Protection of Women from Domestic Violence Act, 2005</div></div>
    <div class="right-card"><div class="rc-tag" style="background:rgba(124,58,237,.15);color:var(--purple);">Police Rights</div><div class="rc-title">Zero FIR — File Anywhere in India</div><div class="rc-text">You can file an FIR at ANY police station regardless of jurisdiction. Police CANNOT refuse — doing so is a criminal offense under Section 166A IPC. They must register and transfer it.</div><div class="rc-year">Criminal Procedure Code — 2013 Amendment</div></div>
    <div class="right-card"><div class="rc-tag" style="background:rgba(255,214,0,.15);color:var(--yellow);">Survivor Rights</div><div class="rc-title">Statement at Home — Assault Survivors</div><div class="rc-text">A survivor cannot be called to a police station alone at night. Her statement is recorded at home by a magistrate. Her identity cannot be revealed by police or media under any circumstances.</div><div class="rc-year">Section 164 CrPC + IPC Section 228A</div></div>
    <div class="right-card"><div class="rc-tag" style="background:rgba(0,230,118,.15);color:var(--green);">Legal Aid</div><div class="rc-title">Right to Free Legal Representation</div><div class="rc-text">Every woman victim of crime gets completely free legal services — advocate, court fees, and documentation — from the District Legal Services Authority. Call 15100 or visit any district court in MP.</div><div class="rc-year">Legal Services Authorities Act, 1987</div></div>
    <div class="right-card"><div class="rc-tag" style="background:rgba(255,112,67,.15);color:var(--orange);">Work Rights</div><div class="rc-title">Maternity Benefits — 26 Weeks</div><div class="rc-text">26 weeks of fully paid maternity leave. No employer can fire or demote a pregnant woman. Nursing breaks must be provided. Work-from-home must be considered on return from leave.</div><div class="rc-year">Maternity Benefit (Amendment) Act, 2017</div></div>
    <div class="right-card"><div class="rc-tag" style="background:rgba(0,188,212,.15);color:var(--teal);">Online Safety</div><div class="rc-title">Cyber Crime Against Women</div><div class="rc-text">Morphed images, cyberstalking, sextortion, and online harassment are punishable with up to 3 years imprisonment and fine. Report at cybercrime.gov.in or 1930. First responders must act within 24 hours.</div><div class="rc-year">IT Act 2000 + IPC Sections 354D, 509</div></div>
    <div class="right-card"><div class="rc-tag" style="background:rgba(255,61,139,.15);color:var(--pink);">Night Safety</div><div class="rc-title">Right to Safe Night Shift Transport</div><div class="rc-text">Women in night shifts must be provided safe cab transport with a female security guard. Employers who fail to ensure safety are liable under the Factories Act and can be reported to the Labour Department.</div><div class="rc-year">Factories Act + Industrial Employment Rules</div></div>
  </div>
</section>

